<br>
Now, you might think, &quot;well, every melee can get exactly the same buffs making the DPS gap % similar&quot;, which is true to an extent. However, this parse was done on, pay attention, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>the class on its own and it's benefits without outside help.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Which means, biased to the bone. I've seen many, many, many parses which show, fully buffed, that a ranger has outdamaged a monk, rogue, and warrior. <br>
<br>
Why wasn't the ranger allowed to self ATK buff? It *IS* part of his class, just because the warrior can't self buff doesn't mean squat.<br>
<br>
The monk was at 46% haste while the others were at 41% haste (I believe rogue was also at 46%, but I'm not positive on that as I am about the monk), so no shit the monk will parse higher. This was done over a 13 hour span.<br>
<br>
Back to self buffing, as a ranger you KNOW how much our eagle eye spell improves archery. It's very noticeable. That's something only we can do, and it's built into our class. The fact that the ranger wasn't allowed to add this buff to himself as well as others goes to show this particular parse is invalid. If I warrior had a self buff that allowed him to increase his hit %, you know he would be pissed if they didn't let him use it.<br>
<br>
All in all, that test is inconclusive and shouldn't even be used. Those numbers don't apply to ANY actual situations, because no ranger in his right mind would go into a fight with no self buffs, period.<br>
<br>
Also, correct me if I'm wrong, but I believe we as rangers have the highest ATK cap, because of our self buffs and GoTF AA's. <br>
<br>
Let me end with this, I could care less if they totally neglect our class on these changes. I'm fine with how we are now. However, let me go ahead and say right now that SoE WILL eventually give hybrids some more disciplines/abilities through tomes. Maybe not on launch day, but over time they'll squeeze some in there.... to &quot;rebalance&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
